TextBlock.TextLine: I supose you intend to bring yd brother over with you, of which yd advise
also how long you intend to stay out, what orders you left RW & in case you
should come to dye (which I pray god for bidd) whether you made an other
or fuither will then what, when you was here 1679 & which I do not doubt
if you have advisted with R.W as may apeare by writing pray excuse
my needless care yett I hope you will take itt asa p. of affection that
I have, because you or yd interressed & freinds should have din for experiency
doth teach us dayly, that what whee least think off most & osten over comes
us or happens to us. whoever when you see our freinds pray remember
mee hertely & lett mee intreat you to spend acrowne for my acctt
fora to aken with mr. Anneslay, collier Buttler, pickering & Ro binson&
inclosed you have yd acctt. as itt was posted & ballanced ult. June last
in mij Bookes where in yd finde creditt for what goods are sold for
us perticular & due to you ƒ 453„ 8½ sence I finde wee don butt little in
the flemish acctt itt beeng all p. ex. & in selling there must come good
to you in the present acctt yd ½ in the bale of kersies N.5 on ely for
the rest is not sold yett the 8 bayes & some hose of which you know
T.S. hath the scharlett with topps: so you can casely make up the acctt
my bookes are yett about 6 weekes behinde in posting, so when you returne itt
shall be altoghether in order, & please to advise if you finde this right
the perticulars shall draw out with the rest, our northen trade is in different
butt not, cleared, so bring to acctt. of which you an happy voage suposeing you
intend bij way of calais which I could advise you to & that you may
prosper in dayes as the saids on the sea shore & finde all to content
& so remaine be mindefull of my intrest with some that
mee in England
In Antwerpen 17 Janu 1680
Brugge Raphael Coots
Mons. in antwoort vanden ul van 15 deses en wille niet twijffelen
oft de 2 packen sijn noch dien dagh ul ter handt gekomen, alsoo den
voormeen het sel ue had belooft, N.6 sal ul op nieuwe poorte neffens
den brief voorts senden en wenste N7 adroiture schep koude voortgaen
geloovende Adriaen blockmet noch niet vertoocken en soo ul
de occasie goedt dunckt ul kan N7 met hem sende, ende het secreteer
hooglijck belasten oock in soo danigh geval mr. vivians adviseeren
heden vertreck p bode costij woch een paxken AV.N.8 dewelck oock
geerne nae london had versonden tsij bij secure occasie van schepen
oft p baequet boot, soo in gevalle het selve met versonden sal
sijn, sal nae gelegenthijt op nieuwe poorte ordonneere, michiel
de kaes was tot ostend gearriveert aen sijn boort sijn 24 p. saen
seyde koussens ick had belast tot londen die hergens doen. in packen
om daer over geen onkoste te loyde twelk suponere eghter wel kan
geschieden want de packagie & quantiteyt seer cleyn is, ende den
schip wel kan verbergen niet te minen soecke geen rusie
de 2 paxken catoene lijne sal tgemoet te sien p dobbelaer
in sijn retour en wensche hertelijck dat ben clarck gearriveert
sij op de gemengelde frisaerde en twee packen kmogen mede
komen, also in tuytterste daer omverlegen ben segge dat ten
packen in geladen p lueyknightley den ur. van 12 courant sijnde
tijt de ontfangen dencke ul. versende van de twee packen tijken de
vrinde geadviseert de onkost Rek sal nae sien &de corantt gemoet
dencke dat de nass gearriveerde goederen met de liiente alleen sullen
belast worden wat passeirt vernemageerne waer mede blijve
In Antwarp 18 Janu 1681
London Henry Maynard
h
my last to you was on the 7: curitt with patternes & instructions to
provide some northren goods besides aperreelle of spanich cloathes the
pattarnes for which I hope you will be mindefull & curious off for
I could desire to have p very first a small bale of the like coleur & I do
in order hereby besides without already in ordered -
1 asN. b
1 asN. c
1 asN. 9 8- of the patt last send to be from 9 to 11 st ayd
these 5 peeces to be packt up with
1asN 1k
1 asN. L
the 4 finist desired least to be asN. b & of 9 st a yd: which will be
3 a 10 quart in one bale vrapped in 2 bayen & sent to mee with all
expedition with the rest may proceed as the concerniency will permitt
besides lett mee know how pack whates sell, for I have
not one peece by mee & that com shall be wanting towards lent
inclosed acctt of sale of last month now expect from Rap coots
mij last acctt of sale charges, as also from gant & then you may verg
speedly exspect yd currant & what more is needfull, now do answer
th
yd of 24 patt De raes is well arrived, butt I did not expect that the hose
should be declared as now they must be I must blame ben klerck for he
neglects the passage where our binlanders do dayly come up had I had
the frises they had been sold ten times & now the winter & season drawes
away I doubt not butt before now you have recd. as well my remise
as the bills sent you for accepted & here you have also yd bill for yd
acctt on mee accepted: the time now is dead in trade & mony so spare
mee & you will have yd needfull towards spring, for I shall do all
endeavours I can to be a remitter because I do not love to be charged
with many bills whoever when you finde that i do not comply
with the articless I shall ul you alwayes lave to demand the
needfull: you have consulted my articles & you allow mee to
demand goods of any other which is well, thought I do not intend
itt in case I can finde our advantage from you butt as to that article
which you supose doth make the aggreement of the 8 monthes to be
of no valuasion you may be confident & really beleave that
thought wee signed no articles, you will finde such due punctuall
complyance with mee in what wee agree that you will never
desire better. I promise to pay the mentioned every monthes sale
8 monthes after itt the restriction I make, is that in case anij man
breaker, though itt, the restriction should be 12„ 15„ 20 monttes after
the sale, I shall finde my garrant from you for yd ½ for you must
not wee have customers that buij now & then, & do onely cleare their
accompts once a yeare, & if they must breake they will not fall
altogheter in a months or 2 time there fore I do desire onely
bj that article delay for such debts as should prove badd afterwards
not that I should pay you onely when they come in because in
yd articles you constringe mee that in case itt prove bad 12 monthes
after the sale so I beleave you understand my meaning
In Antwerpen 20 Ja
Brussel Henrick de senet
Mons. in antwoort vanden ul gedateert 26 Janu hebbe het
bewjshem van twee hondert guldens verloont, doch den vrintsulle
sijnde, heeft gelooft nae gelegentheyt te betaelen soo iets middeltij
tot ul dinst voor valt gelieft te commandeeren, d Engelsch
datinen en sijn tot mijn leet wesen noch niet komen, hope
in korte dagen bij ul te sijn, soo daen entuschen noch iets voorvalt
sal ul geene dienen waermede blijve
